<br>
If anyone was on late last night, you know I bought a Shissar Guardian Staff, with a right-clicky effect of Phantom Plate (lvl 44 mage spell, AC/regen buff, self only).<br>
<br>
Kewl, I thought, mana-free regen and I don't need the gems...$$$.  For only 350pp, for a staff that drops off of VS, $$ i thought.<br>
<br>
Now I didn't have enough time last night to fully test the staff, but upon closer inspection this morning, I read that it still requires the gems, and the only benefit is that it is mana-free.  The only reason I bought it was more for the gem-free cast and not the mana-free cast.<br>
<br>
So this brings up a question.  Are all right-clicky effects that require components still demanding the components to right-click?  Or is it on a case-by-case basis?  <br>
<br>
YOU have gotten better at squandering what little money you had (199)!<br>
